# Claude API Integration Rules — BundleIQ

## SDK Import
```go
import "github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-go"
```
Always use the official `github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-go`. Never use raw `net/http` calls to the API.

## Model
Always use: `anthropic.ModelClaudeSonnet4_5_20250929`
Never hardcode model strings as raw strings — use the SDK constant.

## Client Initialization (in main.go, passed to handlers)
```go
// Client reads ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from environment automatically
client := anthropic.NewClient()
```
The client is initialized ONCE in main.go and passed to the analyzer. Never initialize it per-request.

## Non-Streaming Call Pattern (Triage, Timeline)
```go
func RunTriage(ctx context.Context, client *anthropic.Client, data *bundle.BundleData) (*TriageResult, error) {
    prompt := BuildTriagePrompt(data)
    
    msg, err := client.Messages.New(ctx, anthropic.MessageNewParams{
        Model:     anthropic.ModelClaudeSonnet4_5_20250929,
        MaxTokens: 1024,
        System: []anthropic.TextBlockParam{
            {Text: TriageSystemPrompt},
        },
        Messages: []anthropic.MessageParam{
            anthropic.NewUserMessage(anthropic.NewTextBlock(prompt)),
        },
    })
    if err != nil {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("RunTriage claude call: %w", err)
    }
    
    // Extract text from response
    if len(msg.Content) == 0 {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("RunTriage: empty response from Claude")
    }
    text := msg.Content[0].Text
    
    // Parse JSON — Claude returns JSON inside the text
    var result TriageResult
    if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(text), &result); err != nil {
        // Try to extract JSON from markdown code blocks
        text = extractJSONFromMarkdown(text)
        if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(text), &result); err != nil {
            return nil, fmt.Errorf("RunTriage parse JSON: %w, raw: %.200s", err, text)
        }
    }
    
    return &result, nil
}
```

## Streaming Call Pattern (RCA)
```go
func RunRCA(ctx context.Context, client *anthropic.Client, data *bundle.BundleData, w io.Writer) error {
    prompt := BuildRCAPrompt(data)
    
    stream := client.Messages.NewStreaming(ctx, anthropic.MessageNewParams{
        Model:     anthropic.ModelClaudeSonnet4_5_20250929,
        MaxTokens: 4096,
        System: []anthropic.TextBlockParam{
            {Text: RCASystemPrompt},
        },
        Messages: []anthropic.MessageParam{
            anthropic.NewUserMessage(anthropic.NewTextBlock(prompt)),
        },
    })
    
    for stream.Next() {
        event := stream.Current()
        
        // Check context cancellation on each iteration
        select {
        case <-ctx.Done():
            return ctx.Err()
        default:
        }
        
        switch delta := event.Delta.(type) {
        case anthropic.ContentBlockDeltaEventDelta:
            if delta.Type == "text_delta" {
                if _, err := w.Write([]byte(delta.Text)); err != nil {
                    return fmt.Errorf("write to SSE: %w", err)
                }
            }
        }
    }
    
    if err := stream.Err(); err != nil {
        return fmt.Errorf("RunRCA stream: %w", err)
    }
    
    return nil
}
```

## Error Handling for API Errors
```go
func classifyAPIError(err error) (userMsg string, shouldRetry bool) {
    var apiErr *anthropic.Error
    if !errors.As(err, &apiErr) {
        return "Analysis service unreachable. Please try again.", false
    }
    
    switch apiErr.StatusCode {
    case 429:
        return "Analysis rate limited. Please wait 60 seconds and retry.", false
    case 529:
        return "Analysis service overloaded. Retrying once...", true
    case 401:
        return "API key invalid or missing.", false
    case 400:
        return "Analysis request was malformed (this is a bug, please report it).", false
    default:
        return fmt.Sprintf("Analysis failed (HTTP %d). Please retry.", apiErr.StatusCode), false
    }
}
```

## Retry Logic (529 only)
```go
func withRetry(ctx context.Context, fn func() error) error {
    err := fn()
    if err == nil {
        return nil
    }
    
    var apiErr *anthropic.Error
    if errors.As(err, &apiErr) && apiErr.StatusCode == 529 {
        slog.Warn("Claude overloaded, retrying in 2s")
        select {
        case <-time.After(2 * time.Second):
        case <-ctx.Done():
            return ctx.Err()
        }
        return fn() // one retry only
    }
    
    return err
}
```

## Prompt Construction Rules

### System Prompts (defined as package-level constants)
```go
const TriageSystemPrompt = `You are an expert Kubernetes SRE analyzing a support bundle.
You will receive structured data extracted from a Kubernetes cluster support bundle.
Your job is to identify and prioritize issues.

IMPORTANT: Respond with ONLY valid JSON. No markdown, no explanation, no code blocks.
The JSON must exactly match the schema provided in the user message.`

const RCASystemPrompt = `You are an expert Kubernetes SRE performing root cause analysis.
You will receive structured data from a Kubernetes support bundle.
Your job is to identify the root cause of failures and provide actionable remediation steps.

Format your response as structured markdown with these EXACT sections:
## Root Cause
## Evidence  
## Fix Steps
## Prevention

In Fix Steps, always provide exact kubectl commands. Be specific about namespace and resource names.`
```

### User Prompt Construction
```go
func BuildTriagePrompt(data *bundle.BundleData) string {
    // Serialize the BundleData to JSON for Claude
    dataJSON, _ := json.MarshalIndent(data, "", "  ")
    
    return fmt.Sprintf(`Analyze this Kubernetes support bundle data and return a JSON triage report.

Bundle data:
%s

Return JSON matching exactly this schema:
{
    "severityScore": <0-100, where 100 is completely broken>,
    "summary": "<1-2 sentence overview of cluster health>",
    "clusterHealth": "<one of: critical|degraded|warning|healthy>",
    "affectedNamespaces": ["<namespace>", ...],
    "topIssues": [
        {
            "title": "<short title>",
            "severity": "<critical|high|medium|low>",
            "affectedPod": "<pod name or empty string>",
            "category": "<oom|image-pull|crash-loop|config|resource|network|unknown>"
        }
    ]
}

Return ONLY the JSON. No other text.`, string(dataJSON))
}
```

### Token Budget Check Before API Calls
```go
// In analyzer.go, before any Claude call:
func checkPromptBudget(prompt string, maxChars int) error {
    if len(prompt) > maxChars {
        return fmt.Errorf("prompt too large: %d chars (max %d). Token budget enforcement may have failed", 
            len(prompt), maxChars)
    }
    return nil
}

// Phase budgets (in characters, roughly 4 chars per token):
// Triage:  40,000 chars max
// Timeline: 40,000 chars max
// RCA:     60,000 chars max
// Chat:    20,000 chars max (per message, excluding history)
```

## Chat Conversation Pattern
```go
func RunChat(ctx context.Context, client *anthropic.Client, data *bundle.BundleData, history []ChatMessage, newMsg string) (string, error) {
    // Build system prompt with bundle context
    systemPrompt := fmt.Sprintf(`You are an expert Kubernetes SRE analyzing a specific support bundle.
Only reference information that appears in the bundle data below.
If asked about something not in the bundle, say "I don't see that in this bundle."
Be concise and actionable.

Bundle summary:
%s`, buildChatBundleContext(data))
    
    // Build message history
    messages := make([]anthropic.MessageParam, 0, len(history)+1)
    for _, h := range history {
        if h.Role == "user" {
            messages = append(messages, anthropic.NewUserMessage(anthropic.NewTextBlock(h.Content)))
        } else {
            messages = append(messages, anthropic.NewAssistantMessage(anthropic.NewTextBlock(h.Content)))
        }
    }
    messages = append(messages, anthropic.NewUserMessage(anthropic.NewTextBlock(newMsg)))
    
    msg, err := client.Messages.New(ctx, anthropic.MessageNewParams{
        Model:     anthropic.ModelClaudeSonnet4_5_20250929,
        MaxTokens: 2048,
        System:    []anthropic.TextBlockParam{{Text: systemPrompt}},
        Messages:  messages,
    })
    if err != nil {
        return "", fmt.Errorf("RunChat: %w", err)
    }
    
    if len(msg.Content) == 0 {
        return "", fmt.Errorf("RunChat: empty response")
    }
    
    return msg.Content[0].Text, nil
}

// Build compact bundle context for chat (< 2000 chars)
func buildChatBundleContext(data *bundle.BundleData) string {
    var sb strings.Builder
    fmt.Fprintf(&sb, "Cluster: %s\n", data.ClusterVersion)
    fmt.Fprintf(&sb, "Nodes: %d\n", len(data.NodeSummaries))
    fmt.Fprintf(&sb, "Pods with issues:\n")
    for _, p := range data.PodSummaries {
        if p.Reason != "" {
            fmt.Fprintf(&sb, "  - %s/%s: %s (restarts: %d)\n", p.Namespace, p.Name, p.Reason, p.RestartCount)
        }
    }
    // Add top 5 events
    fmt.Fprintf(&sb, "Recent warning events:\n")
    count := 0
    for _, e := range data.Events {
        if e.Type == "Warning" && count < 5 {
            fmt.Fprintf(&sb, "  - %s: %s\n", e.Reason, e.Message)
            count++
        }
    }
    return sb.String()
}
```

## JSON Extraction Utility
```go
// Claude sometimes wraps JSON in markdown code blocks. Handle both cases.
func extractJSONFromMarkdown(s string) string {
    // Try to find JSON block
    start := strings.Index(s, "```json")
    if start != -1 {
        s = s[start+7:]
        end := strings.Index(s, "```")
        if end != -1 {
            return strings.TrimSpace(s[:end])
        }
    }
    // Try plain ``` block
    start = strings.Index(s, "```")
    if start != -1 {
        s = s[start+3:]
        end := strings.Index(s, "```")
        if end != -1 {
            return strings.TrimSpace(s[:end])
        }
    }
    // Return as-is, trimmed
    return strings.TrimSpace(s)
}
```
